&lt;li&gt;Repair and/or replace any subsystem associated with heavy, medium, and/or light duty SAM coaches and automotive equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other maintenance workers, drivers, and transportation supervisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain relationships with suppliers and vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess knowledge of the design, adjustment, operation, maintenance, and repair of systems and subsystems of SAM coaches and related shop equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work on their feet eight hours per day, lift 100 pounds, and carry parts, equipment, and supplies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess excellent manual dexterity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED equivalent, including trade or vocational school. Additional training at manufacturer’s schools, courses, or seminars is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold a valid SD driver’s license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to obtain a CDL permit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to pass a pre-employment physical&lt;/li&gt;
