&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and inspire a small team of highly skilled AI engineers - setting technical direction, creating space for deep work, and building a culture of ownership, experimentation, and rigorous engineering from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the engineering execution of the AI Labs roadmap - ensuring your team ships production-grade AI products reliably, from problem framing and data pipeline design through to deployment and iteration in live environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay hands-on - contributing directly to architecture decisions, backend systems, and the code that powers AI-driven features at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our customers in a forward-deployed manner to deeply understand problems and constraints and iterate quickly on scalable agentic solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical scoping workshops, directly interfacing with city leaders to solve challenging local problems with agentic workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive engineering across a varied roadmap - spanning data consolidation, predictive modelling, real-time decision-making, and LLM-powered experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate directly with product, data science, and operations teams to identify and prioritize the highest-impact AI opportunities across the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay close to the frontier of AI development and bring new ideas, tools, and approaches into the team proactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
